## Edit Policy

- Automatically fix grammar or formatting only when content meaning is unchanged by the change.
- If changes could alter meaning, offer the change as a suggestion in a comparison table for review before making any changes.
- When content is not clear, ask for clarification before editing.

## Table of contents (TOC)

- Validate that entries for the TOC always comply with the standards explained under Config.md, Paths, and Config paths at https://developer-stage.adobe.com/dev-docs-reference/getting_started/dev-docs/best-practices/
- Mention when Markdown files are not present in the TOC during a validation so the user can decide if they want to add them. This is the highest level of severity during evaluation.

### Instructions for Config.md

The Config.md file is located in the root of the repository and is used to configure the navigation and layout of the microsite.

- In Gatsby, Home is optional and overwrites Products
- In EDS, Products is always displayed and Home must be the first path under Pages

### Instructions for Config paths

- Use absolute prod path for home. Example: [Home](https://developer.adobe.com/your-product/)
- Relative paths should be relative to path prefix and not start with "/". Example: [Getting Started](guides/getting-started/index.md)
- Landing page (the page of the path-prefix) will not have side nav.
- On any parent section page (like /guides/, /community/, etc.), the sidebar navigation automatically displays all the child pages within that section. For example, in the config.md, if there is any subpages (eg. /guides/code-contribution) which is within the same parent section, the sidenav will show up. This contextual sidebar appears for any page that has sub-pages, helping users easily navigate through related content without having to go back to higher-level pages. Example: https://developer-stage.adobe.com/dev-docs-reference/blocks/

## Instructions for Paths

- Use absolute paths when linking to other repos
- Use absolute paths when linking to DevBiz
- Use relative paths when linking within repo
- Relative paths should be relative to path prefix
- Relative links should include file name and extension (example: index.md or other .md file) except for anchor links that are in the current page (example: [description](#anchor)).

## Pasted content

### Content from Microsoft Loop

- Translate the formatting from Microsoft Loop to GitHub-flavored Markdown.
- Where MD conventions are found in the pasted Loop content, apply the conventions to the MD content.
- Ignore any active comments attached to content in the Loop file. Do not include the comments or alter content based on the active comments.

### Content from wiki

- Paste only the page content. Do not include breadcrumbs, wiki navigation information, or page tree information.
